+# Frozen Burden Columns Do Not Rescue Step-008 Without Temporal Architecture And Bridge
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` Step-008 coherence verdict
+
+The Step-008 one-ledger screen does succeed at freezing burden columns as
+categories. The local record cleanly names extraction and stability, temporal
+normalization, LEI compatibility, prior-art overlap, and packaging robustness
+as separate burdens to audit.
+
+That organization still does not make the setup live.
+
+Why the branch remains blocked:
+
+- no local source freezes one actual temporal architecture on the inherited
+  suitable-weak / Leray-Hopf plus LEI floor;
+- no explicit bridge carries that floor into a later critical-element or
+  compactness-rigidity program;
+- and no mixed bridge architecture is locally supported as a replacement.
+
+So Step-008 should not be read as "the ledger is organized, therefore the
+program is coherent." The correct verdict remains:
+`setup obstruction, branch should stop before host-space audit`.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-008-exploration-002-one-ledger-coherence.md`
